IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER:

This software implements international electrical engineering standards including:
- IEC 60364-5-52 (Cable selection and voltage drop)
- IEC 60909-0 (Short-circuit current calculation)
- IEEE Std 399 (Power system analysis)
- IEEE 1584-2018 (Arc flash hazard calculation)
- NFPA 70E (Electrical safety in the workplace)

The use of this software does NOT replace the need for review and approval by a
licensed professional engineer. All electrical designs must be reviewed, stamped,
and approved by a qualified professional engineer licensed in the relevant
jurisdiction before implementation.

Users of this software assume full responsibility for:
- Verifying all calculations and results
- Ensuring compliance with local codes and regulations
- Obtaining proper professional engineering review and approval
- Safe implementation of any designs

The authors and copyright holders assume no liability for any damages, injuries,
or losses resulting from the use of this software.
